text:
="preserve">Sjarifuddin Baharsjah (16 May 1931 – 14 January 2021) was an Indonesian politician and academic. He was born in West Java, Indonesia. From 1993 to 1998, he was Minister of Agriculture during the Suharto cabinet. He was married to Justika Baharsjah.
Baharsjah died on 14 January 2021 in Jakarta at the age of 89.
